news.title: Smartworks receives SEBI approval for IPO
news.para: Smartworks, a flexible workspace provider, has received SEBI approval for its IPO. The company operates in 13 cities in India and has expanded to Singapore. Keppel Ltd. is a major investor in Smartworks, having invested $29 million.

news.title: Promoters, Warburg Pincus' arm sell 19.6% stake in Home First Finance for Rs 1,728 crore
news.para: As per the bulk deal data available on the exchange, Orange Clove Investments sold 94.42 shares, or 10.6 per cent stake, in Home First Finance, while True North Fund offloaded 48.09 lakh shares, amounting to a 5.4 per cent stake in the company.

news.title: Shriram Properties' CMD gets Sebi's approval for indirect acquisition
news.para: Malayappan owns 0.08% of smallcap company Shriram Properties, whose market capitalisation is at Rs 1,874 crore.

news.title: Ventive Hospitality receives Sebi's approval for Rs 2,000 crore IPO
news.para: Ventive Hospitality, a Blackstone-backed company, has received SEBI approval for a Rs 2,000 crore IPO. The company focuses on luxury hospitality, operating properties under brands like Marriott, Hilton, and Anantara. Ventive's portfolio includes 11 assets with 2,036 keys across India and the Maldives.

news.title: Shraddha Kapoor rents 3,929 sq ft apartment in Mumbai’s Juhu
news.para: Shraddha Kapoor has rented this apartment spread over nearly 3,929 sq ft on the third floor of a luxury residential tower for a total term of 12 months.

news.title: Maharashtra RERA to appoint retired tehsildars for recovery in Mumbai and Pune
news.para: In Mumbai suburban, approximately Rs 228 crore is yet to be recovered from 355 complaints of 73 projects, while in Pune district, the amount stands at Rs 150.7 crore from 201 complaints of 89 projects.

news.title: Godrej Properties raises Rs 6,000 crore through QIP
news.para: In a regulatory filing on Monday, Godrej Properties informed that the board's QIP Placement Committee approved the closure of the issue on Monday.

news.title: Bank of America leases 1.60 lakh sq ft office for Rs 350 crore in Mumbai’s Powai
news.para: As per the agreement, it holds an option to pick up additional 1 lakh sq ft spanning two floors taking the total size of the deal to 250,000 sq ft and rental payout to Rs 600 crore.

news.title: I-T raids on three Gujarat builders yield Rs 10 crore
news.para: The search started on Saturday at the premises of a Mehsana-based real estate developer group, which has several schemes on SG Road, SP Ring Road and Vaishnodevi area in the city.

news.title: ETRealty Real Estate Awards 2025 4th Edition: Nomination forms now open!!!
news.para: Get ready for the ultimate celebration of innovation and excellence in India's real estate sector!

news.title: NGT issues notices over encroachment on Luna riverbed in Odisha
news.para: Notices have also been sent to the member secretary of Odisha State Pollution Control Board and State Environment Impact Assessment Authority.

news.title: Real estate receives Rs 75,468 crore investments from AIFs in H1 FY25: Report
news.para: In the first nine months of this year alone, the real estate sector saw Rs 28,560 crore raised through private equity investments, according to Anarock Capital.

news.title: Macrotech Developers acquires 45-acre land in Gurugram for Rs 110 crore
news.para: Mumbai-based Macrotech Developers, which sells properties under the Lodha brand, is one of the leading real estate developers in the country.

news.title: Noida: Authorities demolish illegal sand mining road across Yamuna river
news.para: The road had been laid by tethering wooden planks to the river bed, filling them up with sandbags and then with sand to make it look like any other part of the heavily silted river.

news.title: Netherlands's ABP acquires $2.8 billion in mortgage loans
news.para: ABP, the largest Dutch pension fund with around 530 billion euros in assets, said the mortgage loans had been granted in the past 5 years to around 10,000 households in the Netherlands.

news.title: Tripura: 25 families of Reang tribe to receive pucca houses under PMAY
news.para: ​​Reang is a Particularly Vulnerable Tribal Group (PVTG) in Tripura and its members traditionally live in 'tong ghars' (makeshift huts) on the slopes of hilly terrain and keep changing their houses for jhuming (shifting cultivation) as it is their main source of livelihood.

news.title: Maharashtra RERA recovers over Rs 200 crore from developers to compensate homebuyers
news.para: ​​ The real estate watchdog said it has issued 1,163 warrants for recovering Rs 705.62 crore across the state and has made developers cough up Rs 200.23 crore from 283 warrants involving 139 real estate projects, as per an official statement.

news.title: New home prices in China rise 0.36% in November 2024
news.para: The average price across 100 cities edged up 0.36%, compared with the previous month's 0.29%, according to data released by property researcher China Index Academy.

news.title: Bhubaneswar: Homebuyers of Dhauli Heights face further delay in allotment
news.para: Responding to queries raised by different MLAs in the assembly on the status of allotment of houses in Dhauli Heights, the minister recently stated that Odisha Police Housing and Welfare Corporation (OPHWC) completed the construction and handed over the project to OCHC

news.title: Pune: Residents, developers urge approval of development plan for merged villages
news.para: The planned development in the 11 villages merged with PMC seven years ago is on a slow track. On the other hand, unauthorised constructions and encroachments are rampant.
